Really good food and a large hot, prepared section. Nice seating area also. Only problem is the employees are terrible. Rude and not helpful at all. The last time I was there I stopped in for lunch before a business meeting & as I was grabbing a drink from the back cooler an employee stocking the shelves dropped two cans of Coke. They broke open and sprayed soda all over my pants, shirt & shoes. All over.. The guy just looked down at the mess and at me and then just mumbled something to himself and kept stocking the last few things. No apology, no recognition of it even happening, nothing. A girl next to me looked at me and laughed and said "this place is the worst" so I guess this kind of rudeness was normal. The guy at the checkout saw this happening and I assumed he would comment on it when I got up to the register he never even looked up. Just ran my card. So that was the last time I went there. There are plenty of other options in the area. Too bad because they do have good food.

This deli shows no kindness and offers no help to customers in need of help. On the verge of suffering from heat exhaustion and low blood sugar I stumbled into the store, grabbed a water bottle and collapsed at a table. A few minutes later a staff came over, and told me "you can't sit here all day." At that point I was still sweating heavily and feeling nauseous, so I went to the bathroom to recover. The same staff chased me down, knocked on the door, and demanded I come out of the bathroom. When I eventually did, he reminded me I still hadn't paid for the water and nonchalantly told me to never come back if I'm angry with how I'm treated.  No one, no one, deserves to be treated this inhumanely in times of need. This place should not exist. And this  neighborhood will be better off without this cruel and unforgiving institution that can't even let someone sick to just sit down and rest.
